How Worried Should We Be About Screen Time During the Pandemic?

ops.insert: Living through the pandemic meant that so much more of our lives moved online. Recreation, social meetings, work - has all increasingly moved online over the course of the last 2-3 years. This encourages us to have a sedentary lifestyle. While earlier you would take some time in between your day to maybe walk to another building for a meeting, now we'd just hop on Zoom instead.
We all developed hobbies which we were able to take up over the web and this changes the profile of how we spend our time.
